  "_about": "Curated lexicon of magical vocabulary. Each root maps to a regex matching its morphological variants (inflections + derivations). 'category' groups roots into site sections; 'gloss' is a one-line sense for the site + podcast. Human-reviewable on purpose. Patterns are wrapped in \\b(?:...)\\b and matched case-insensitively by analyze.py. Scope note (Ted 2026-07-08): core magic stays TIGHT, but explicit themed sections added for alchemy, divination, classical magical items (historical magic, NOT modern-fantasy coinages), and history-of-the-book terms. Roots with 0 corpus hits simply don't render.",
  "_caveats": {
    "herbal": "adjective 'herbal' inflates the book sense; flavor/rules split helps",
    "testament": "catches 'Testament' (scripture) + wills; historical book sense is a subset",
    "phylactery": "Greek phylakterion = amulet/scroll-case (historical); D&D lich sense is modern — good etymology-episode fodder",
    "fetish": "Portuguese feitiço, a genuine historical-magic object term; modern sense may add noise",
    "divine": "adjective 'divine' overlaps the divination verb; expected"
  },
